<topic id='class_lodged_patient.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Class: LODGED PATIENT - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 temporarily accommodated in an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 or elsewhere for whom a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_decision_to_admit">DECISION TO ADMIT</xref>
 has been made; but who remains waiting in the nursing care of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 for longer than is appropriate for his/her condition before moving to a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>This occurs in cases where:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
Pre-arrangements have been made for movement to a 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
, or        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
A 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_decision_to_admit">DECISION TO ADMIT</xref>
 has been made as a result of an 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_attendance">Accident and Emergency Attendance</xref>
. Any facility set up to treat emergency and/or walk in cases is regarded as an 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_accident_and_emergency_department">Accident and Emergency Department</xref>
 for this purpose.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>

</body>
